J621kwxhpsKg4k_qS0jTnOcsFavnbWB9c_7s5dHac2m0TDRpR7SHbKmfHBDsyJthhUQwJjwQC74VgmQ9VUdH0eh8-EvMDnBQmuEIs=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating nested classes in JUnit**\\n\\nI’m thinking it may not consider nested classes as roots without the @Nested annotation. The scanner's method is for finding nested classes after identifying the outer class. But can JUnit Platform detect a nested static class like TestClassScannerTest$ClassTemplateSpringTestCase? If the class is static and nested, it seems only to discover nested classes within enclosing top-level classes. Maybe it’s better to use a separate top-level fixture class, since Java permits one public and multiple package-private classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring test class discovery**\\n\\nI'm thinking that if I put `@ClassTemplate @ExtendWith({SpringExtension.class, SingleInvocationProvider.class})` above my class definition for ClassTemplateSpringTestCase and make it a top-level package-private class, JUnit should be able to discover it during scanning. This class resides in our package, separate from libraries, which is good! However, the filename is TestClassScannerTest.java, and it raises questions about naming—especially since it doesn’t have a \\\"Test\\\" suffix. Hmm, will JUnit discover it if it has @ClassTemplate? It's likely yes!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test runners**\\n\\nI need to consider whether to use Vintage for the existing SpringJUnit4ClassRunnerTest. It seems like the test is using Jupiter to instantiate the runner. I should read more about this to clarify my approach. It looks like there's a connection between how Vintage and Jupiter handle these tests, and getting that right could really help ensure the tests work smoothly. I'll explore this further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Udw6M1RSin45JgVMk9L7draC|fc_0f0e3408191c9cfe016a282234b76c8196bc1a2d0f1c0f4ff8", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/SpringJUnit4ClassRunnerTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1078, "output": 2148, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41114, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781015039340, "responseId": "resp_0f0e3408191c9cfe016a2821ffc9f88196be13f97418fcb54c"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Udw6M1RSin45JgVMk9L7draC|fc_0f0e3408191c9cfe016a282234b76c8196bc1a2d0f1c0f4ff8", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework.spring_test;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.runner.Description;\nimport org.junit.runners.model.InitializationError;\n\nimport org.springframework.test.context.junit4.SpringJUnit4ClassRunner;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class SpringJUnit4ClassRunnerTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsRunnerForJUnit4TestClass() throws InitializationError {\n        SpringJUnit4ClassRunner runner = new SpringJUnit4ClassRunner(PlainJUnit4TestCase.class);\n\n        Description description = runner.getDescription();\n\n        assertThat(description.getTestClass()).isEqualTo(PlainJUnit4TestCase.class);\n        assertThat(description.getChildren()).hasSize(1);\n        assertThat(description.getChildren().get(0).getMethodName()).isEqualTo(\"sampleTest\");\n    }\n\n    public static class PlainJUnit4TestCase {\n        @org.junit.Test\n        public void sampleTest() {\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781015093072}]}
